# Test: CapReturnDoesNotLeakToPriorSale
# Purpose: a capital return cannot alter the cost of a disposal made before it
# Rules Tested: Section 104 Pooling, Capital Return (TCGA92/S122)
#
#   Buy 100 @ £10 -> pool 100 shares, cost £1,000
#   Sell 50 @ £12 (before the capital return):
#     Cost: 50 x £10 = £500.00, Gain: £100.00
#   Capital return £50 -> remaining pool cost £450 (50 shares)
#   Sell 50 @ £12 (after the capital return):
#     Cost: £450.00, Gain: £150.00
#   The first sale's cost stays £500 - the later capital return does not leak back.
2024-01-01 BUY LEAK 100 @ 10
2024-06-01 SELL LEAK 50 @ 12
2025-01-01 CAPRETURN LEAK 50 TOTAL 50 FEES 0
2025-06-01 SELL LEAK 50 @ 12
